from keras.layers import Input, Dense, LSTM, Reshape, Concatenate, concatenate
from keras.models import Model
import tensorflow as tf
import dataiku

# Define the keras architecture of your model in 'build_model' and return it. Compilation must be done in 'compile_model'.
#   input_shapes  - dictionary of shapes per input as defined in features handling
#   n_classes - For classification, number of target classes


def build_model(input_shapes, n_classes=None):
    print("input_shapes", input_shapes)

    # This input will receive all the preprocessed features
    window_size = dataiku.get_custom_variables(typed=True)["window_size"]

    #input_main = Input(shape=input_shapes["main"], name="main")
    input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed = Input(shape=(window_size,), name="past_ave_temp_preprocessed")
    input_past_high_temp_preprocessed = Input(shape=(window_size,), name="past_high_temp_preprocessed")
    input_past_low_temp_preprocessed = Input(shape=(window_size,), name="past_low_temp_preprocessed")
    input_past_precip_preprocessed = Input(shape=(window_size,), name="past_precip_preprocessed")
    input_past_daylight_preprocessed = Input(shape=(window_size,), name="past_daylight_preprocessed")

    inputs = [
        # input_main,
        input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed, 
        input_past_high_temp_preprocessed,
        input_past_low_temp_preprocessed,
        input_past_precip_preprocessed,
        input_past_daylight_preprocessed
             ]    
    
    # input_main = Reshape((1, 1))(input_main)
    # print("input_main", input_main)
    input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed = Reshape((window_size, 1))(input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed)
    input_past_high_temp_preprocessed = Reshape((window_size, 1))(input_past_high_temp_preprocessed)
    input_past_low_temp_preprocessed = Reshape((window_size, 1))(input_past_low_temp_preprocessed)
    input_past_precip_preprocessed = Reshape((window_size, 1))(input_past_precip_preprocessed)
    input_past_daylight_preprocessed = Reshape((window_size, 1))(input_past_daylight_preprocessed)
    
    print("shape of input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed", input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed.shape)
    
    inputs_reshaped = [
        # input_main,
        input_past_ave_temp_preprocessed, 
        input_past_high_temp_preprocessed,
        input_past_low_temp_preprocessed,
        input_past_precip_preprocessed,
        input_past_daylight_preprocessed
    ]
    
    x_concatenated = Concatenate(axis=-1)(inputs_reshaped)
    print("x_concatenated", x_concatenated.shape)
    #x_reshaped = Reshape((30, 5))(x_concatenated)
    #print("reshape of x", x_reshaped.shape)
    x = LSTM(window_size, return_sequences=True)(x_concatenated)
    x = LSTM(window_size, return_sequences=False)(x)
    predictions = Dense(1)(x)

    model = Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=predictions)
    print("model is", model)

    return model

# Compile your model and return it
#   model   - model defined in 'build_model'
def compile_model(model):
    print('compiling model')
    
    # The loss function depends on the type of problem you solve.
    # 'mse' is appropriate for a regression.
    model.compile(optimizer='rmsprop',
                  loss='mse')

    return model
